 \mathrm E(s^X)=\prod_{k=1}^6\frac{\frac{k}6s}{1-(1-\frac{k}6)s}=\frac{5!}{6^5}s^6\cdot\prod_{k=1}^5\frac1{1-\frac{k}6s}. 
 \prod_{k=1}^5\frac1{1-\frac{k}6s}=\sum_{k=1}^5\frac{c_k}{1-\frac{k}6s},\qquad c_k=\prod_{1\leqslant i\leqslant 5}^{i\ne k}\frac1{1-\frac{i}k}, 
 \mathrm E(s^X)=\frac{5!}{6^5}s^6\cdot\sum_{k=1}^5c_k\sum_{n\geqslant0}\left(\frac{k}6s\right)^n. 
 \mathbb P(X=n+6)=\frac{5!}{6^5}\cdot\sum_{k=1}^5c_k\left(\frac{k}6\right)^n. 
